.SH NAME
svc_rdma_xdr_decode_req \- Decode the transport header
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_rdma_xdr_decode_req
.BI "(struct xdr_buf *rq_arg "  ","
.BI "struct svc_rdma_recv_ctxt *rctxt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rq_arg" 12
xdr_buf containing ingress RPC/RDMA message
.IP "rctxt" 12
state of decoding
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
On entry, xdr->head[0].iov_base points to first byte of the
RPC-over-RDMA transport header.

On successful exit, head[0] points to first byte past the
RPC-over-RDMA header. For RDMA_MSG, this is the RPC message.

The length of the RPC-over-RDMA header is returned.

Assumptions:
- The transport header is entirely contained in the head iovec.
